wp constrain dimensions "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=======================================================================

NAME
----

wp constrain dimensions - Calculates the new dimensions for a down sampled image.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Calculates the new dimensions for a down sampled image.

If either width or height are empty, no constraint is applied on that
dimension.

USAGE
-----

` <?php wp_constrain_dimensions( $current_width, $current_height, $max_width, $max_height ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$current_width` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Current width of the image.
    Default: *None*

 `$current_height` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Current height of the image.
    Default: *None*

 `$max_width` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Maximum wanted width.
    Default: 0

 `$max_height` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional. Maximum wanted height.
    Default: 0

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(array)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   First item is the width, the second item is the height.

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`wp_constrain_dimensions()` is located in `wp-includes/media.php`

